Three young men, who are suspected to be human parts harvesters, have been arrested in Taraba State.It was gathered that the suspects were arrested by officials of the Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps. At the point of their arrest, it was learnt that the suspects were discovered with three human dry bones.The suspects were arrested at Gembu town, headquarters of Sardauna Local Government Area of the state.Spokesperson for the agency, Godwin Peter, confirmed the arrest to SaharaReporters, saying, “Yes, three persons were arrested at Sardauna Local Government Area of the state by our men, they were caught with human bones, they are into selling human bones. “They were arrested on Tuesday, March 1, 2022.”